.TH "i915_gem_fence_alignment" 9 "i915_gem_fence_alignment" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i915_gem_fence_alignment \- required global GTT alignment for a fence
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u32" i915_gem_fence_alignment
.BI "(struct drm_i915_private *i915 "  ","
.BI "u32 size "  ","
.BI "unsigned int tiling "  ","
.BI "unsigned int stride "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "i915" 12
i915 device
.IP "size" 12
object size
.IP "tiling" 12
tiling mode
.IP "stride" 12
tiling stride
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return the required global GTT alignment for a fence (a view of a tiled
object), taking into account potential fence register mapping.
